{{Top|leg}}
The '''Annual Mid-Rim Domesticated Sub-Sentient Show''' was a show for the best sub-sentient creatures in the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]]. It was held annually in [[Munto]], [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]].

==History==
In one unusual year, a [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] [[wilwog]] named [[Itipiniwi]] was awarded first prize of Best in Show. The owner got excited, exciting Itipiniwi, which also annoyed the runner-up's creature, a [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] [[bolstyngar]] named [[Boshuda]]. Boshuda ate Itipiniwi and because rules never dealt with the consumption of the winner by the runner-up, the runner-up was declared the winner due to forfeit.

